snippet.textDisplay: Do a reaction to the Netflix documentary drama, The Irishman! The amount of visual effects, VFX leaps and bounds, overcoming the drastic age dilemma for the cast and how much new tech and software they had to create in order to literally transform these famous actors into a version of their younger self is astounding! Between the cameras themselves, the custom camera rigs, using no facial markers whatsoever on the actors, light scanning technology and inferred recording they managed to create a break through in the film industry and create new visual effects while they were making this documentary drama. It will no doubt forever change the future for VFX.
snippet.textOriginal: Do a reaction to the Netflix documentary drama, The Irishman! The amount of visual effects, VFX leaps and bounds, overcoming the drastic age dilemma for the cast and how much new tech and software they had to create in order to literally transform these famous actors into a version of their younger self is astounding! Between the cameras themselves, the custom camera rigs, using no facial markers whatsoever on the actors, light scanning technology and inferred recording they managed to create a break through in the film industry and create new visual effects while they were making this documentary drama. It will no doubt forever change the future for VFX.

snippet.textDisplay: I swear, I've seen so many effects - many far, far newer and better than the balrog. But when I saw the balrog, I was absolutely blown away. Even on the small screen, it looks real. Not real in the way that other CG characters look, where there's no actual flaws but your brain still knows it's fake. Real.
snippet.textOriginal: I swear, I've seen so many effects - many far, far newer and better than the balrog. But when I saw the balrog, I was absolutely blown away. Even on the small screen, it _looks real._ Not real in the way that other CG characters look, where there's no actual flaws but your brain still knows it's fake. _Real._
